news.title: Ghaziabad development body cancels two layout maps of projects on farmers' land
news.para: The inquiry against the developers was carried out on a complaint by councillor Rajendra Tyagi, who claimed that a group of farmers from Dundahera village had come to him alleging that the two developers had included their land in the layout plans and got them illegally approved by some officials of the town and country planning department.

news.title: Companies should float their own NBFCs to fund road construction related projects: Nitin Gadkari
news.para: "Infrastructure companies are now investing huge money on infrastructure... Infrastructure companies should also float their own non-banking financial companies (NBFCs) to fund road construction related projects," he said while speaking at an Assocham event.

news.title: ACC's net profit declines 29.5% to Rs 396.33 crore in Jan-March 2022
news.para: The company, which follows the January-December financial year, had posted a profit of Rs 562.59 crore a year ago, ACC -- a subsidiary of Swiss building material major Holcim group (Earlier LafargeHolcim) -- said in a BSE filing.

news.title: Energy conservation norms may be must for residential buildings
news.para: It is expected to increase the cost of construction by 2-3% but the recovery takes place within 4-5 years through reduced electricity bills, a senior government official said. The code will be applicable on new residential complexes consuming 100 KW load, typically societies with 20 1BHKs or 10 2BHKs, he said.

news.title: Motilal Oswal PE arm to invest Rs 2,000 crore in 2022-23
news.para: The company disbursed ₹1,500 crore in 2021-22 and with developers launching more projects, the company expects an increase in demand for capital as well. During this fiscal year, the business also plans to create its sixth real estate fund.

news.title: After boycott call, Haryana RERA chief meets RWAs to set conclave agenda
news.para: The seminar cum workshop cum conference (SEWOCON) is being organised by H-Rera and DTCP on April 29. On Tuesday, H-Rera had a lengthy discussion with the representatives of RWAs of group housing societies, private plotted colonies and HSVP sectors.

news.title: Grant loans to realty sector after ensuring government approvals for project: RBI to NBFCs
news.para: Besides, the regulator said NBFCs should not grant loans and advances totalling Rs 5 crore and above to their own directors, including the chairman and managing director or their relatives and other related entities.

news.title: HDFC divests 1% stake in Ansal Housing for nearly Rs 49 lakh
news.para: ​According to bulk deal data available with the NSE, Housing Development Finance Corporation Ltd (HDFC) sold a total of 5,74,726 shares, amounting to 0.96 per cent stake of Ansal Housing Ltd.

news.title: U.S. home builder sentiment hits seven-month low in April: NAHB
news.para: The housing market is under the spotlight as the Federal Reserve adopts an aggressive monetary policy stance in its fight against sky-high inflation, sending the 30-year fixed mortgage rate above 5% for first time in over a decade.

news.title: Turkey's house price index surges 96% annually in February
news.para: In the country's largest city Istanbul, home to around a fifth of Turkey's population of 85 million, the index climbed 106.3% on the year.

news.title: Max Ventures and Industries to amalgamate with subsidiary Max Estates
news.para: ​Its board had then authorised the Investment and Finance Committee to explore various modalities for restructuring with Max Estates Ltd and be renamed as Max Estates after receiving the required statutory approvals.

news.title: China developers speed up diversification after debt-led growth fuels crisis
news.para: KWG Group Holdings, CIFI Holdings and state-backed China Resources Land were among developers that listed diversification plans along with their recent financial results.

news.title: Builders fear non-completion of projects unless raw material costs are controlled
news.para: ​Releasing its report titled 'National Price Rise Impact Study 2022', Credai National President Harsh Vardhan Patodia said housing prices have increased 5-8 per cent due to rise in cost of construction and rates are expected to rise further by 5-7 per cent, taking the total increase to 10-15 per cent across India.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers' sales bookings up 45% to Rs 1,739 crore in FY22
news.para: In terms of sales volumes, the company sold 2.71 million square feet in 2021-22 from 2.08 million square feet in the previous year. The average realisation increased 11 per cent to Rs 6,407 per square feet from Rs 5,785 per square feet.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh to spend Rs 13,000 crore on housing scheme
news.para: The chief minister also told the officials to construct storage points in the layouts given to the beneficiaries. He also told the officials to find alternative sites to be given as some of the layouts are in court disputes.
